text\":\"**Assessing runtime arguments**\\n\\nSo, I’ve realized that the condition checks for libraryVersion being '5.0.0', which means there won't be any runtime arguments for 5.0.1, leading to potential failures. For the generated tests or native tests, I need to set the same runtime JVM arguments for 5.0.1 because it relies on specific Netty versions and their reflective memory access on Java 25 native runs. I should ensure we’re using localhost for testing and avoid external services, focusing on maintaining system properties.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 is usable with its normal transitive dependencies and can be meaningfully covered with an in-process Vert.x HTTP server, but its Vert.x core dependency resolves Netty 4.2.2.Final, so Java 25 native-image runs need the same Netty unsafe-access system properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set native test runtime system properties for the 5.0.1 test scaffold: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Tests can use Vertx.vertx(), an in-process HttpServer bound to 127.0.0.1 with an ephemeral port, and WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient against that server; no external service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The unsafe-access properties are tied to Java 25/native-image current-defaults behavior and should still be validated by the authoritative Gradle native test.\",\n    \"Avoid depending on internet endpoints; local in-process HTTP coverage is enough for normal WebClient request, response, multipart, redirect, cookie, and caching paths.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02d1c4cbadfb1aba016a3f60b8e0b481939023d28c7fcc3c34\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3138, "output": 791, "cacheRead": 16896, "cach